-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP: Aecon, Cascades, Bombardier 
-- 
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 05:57AM EST
-- None



Jan 22 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Aecon and Cascades, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Aecon <ARE.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold  * Cascades <CAS.TO>: NBF removes from action list; keeps outperform rating  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Aecon <ARE.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold  * Aecon <ARE.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises price target to C$20 from C$14  * Bird Construction <BDT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity ups target to C$14.50 from C$13; rating buy * Bombardier <BBDb.TO>: CIBC cuts target price to C$5 from C$5.75; sector outperformer  * Cascades <CAS.TO>: NBF removes from action list; keeps outperform rating * Detour Gold <DGC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$4.50 from C$4.25; rating sell * Finning International <FTT.TO>: Canaccord ups target to C$31 from C$29; rating buy * Gran Tierra Energy <GTE.TO>: Canaccord Genuity ups target to C$9.50 from C$9; rating buy * IAMGOLD Corp <IMG.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy  * Newalta Corp <NAL.TO>: NBF raises target price to C$21 from C$19; rating outperform * Toromont Industries <TIH.TO>: Canaccord Genuity ups target toC$29.50 from C$27.50; buy * Transat AT <TRZb.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target to C$18.50 from C$19.25; rating buy* WSP Global <WSP.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$31.50 from C$25.50; rating hold